A four-year-old boy is in a critical condition after a near-drowning incident in Mooirivier Road in Norkem Park, Johannesburg, on Saturday afternoon, paramedics said. ER24 paramedics were called to the scene by local security services, ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said. Upon arrival, paramedics found security officers performing cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) on a young boy lying next to the pool. ER24 paramedics immediately took over the treatment and provided the child with several advanced life support interventions. After a few short minutes the child s vital signs returned. The toddler was transported to a nearby park where they were met by a medical helicopter to airlift the patient to a private hospital for urgent treatment. The details surrounding the incident were not yet known, Meiring said.